<p itemprop="description">Communicating between the technical and non-technical involves translating complex technical concepts into clear, accessible language for diverse audiences, and facilitating understanding between technical and business stakeholders.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can recognise when technical communication needs to be adapted for different audiences and understand the importance of clear communication.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can explain technical concepts in simple terms and adapt your communication style for different stakeholders.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can facilitate complex technical discussions with mixed audiences, create effective technical documentation for various stakeholders, and bridge communication gaps between teams.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead cross-functional communication strategies, mentor others in technical communication, and establish communication standards that work across technical and business domains.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

